Class MeterReading

java.lang.Object
com.kf7014.smartcitymicroservice.model.MeterReading
@CompoundIndex(name="provider_meter_timestamp_idx",def="{'providerId': 1, 'meterId': 1, 'timestamp': 1}",unique=true) @CompoundIndex(name="provider_timestamp_idx",def="{'providerId': 1, 'timestamp': -1}") public class MeterReading extends Object
Represents a meter reading submitted by a specific provider.

This model maps to the meter_readings collection in MongoDB and includes details such as provider ID, meter ID, reading value, timestamp, and a flag indicating if the reading was submitted manually.

Compound indexes are defined to optimize query performance and enforce uniqueness where necessary.
